column35:
In the OCI Console, for MySQL databases, the SQL Worksheet doesn't correctly render values whose types are JSON objects.

For example, take the following statement:
{code:java}
SELECT JSON_OBJECT("key", "value") AS RESULT;
{code}


At present in production this is the result of the execution:
{code:java}
RESULT
---------------
[object Object]
{code}


The expected result is this:
{code:java}
RESULT          
--------------- 
{"key":"value"} 
{code}

----

The fix for this issue consists in the following:
- Upgrade the version of the "oj-dbt-data-grid" component to the latest available in the "master" branch of SDW (currently 1.0.18).
- Cherry pick the changes of merge request [11994|https://orahub.oci.oraclecorp.com/database-dbtools-dev/rest-data-services/-/merge_requests/11994] that are related to the Script Output panel.

